The paper deals with optimization problems related to order picking in warehouses, which is a common problem in operations research (cs.OR). The paper also proposes algorithms based on mixed-integer programming and dynamic programming, which are common techniques in computer science subfields such as algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
